rio finds a natural place in our current vision of\nthe early solar system when conditions were favorable for giant collisions to\noccur. The next step in exploration of Martian moon is a sample return mission\nto test the giant collision scenario for their origin, and to provide tests of\nmodels of early solar system dynamics since Mars may retain material exchanged\nbetween the inner and outer solar system.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Sep 2019 17:16:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-21"}
