e Carlo samples that the fields and couplings can be well\nrecovered, but that recovering the pairwise correlations in the resolution of a\ntotal energy is harder for the natural proteins than for the protein-like\nsequences. Selective temperature for folding/structural constrains in protein\nevolution is also estimated.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Sep 2019 08:41:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 26 May 2020 04:47:06 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 18 Jun 2021 05:41:55 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sat, 2 Oct 2021 02:18:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-05"}
